data.name: RichTextBox1.Text
data.value:
"Why I created this IDE and how I got the opportunity to work on it...
Well, it's a long story but one I'm going to tell. I have always wanted to make my own Android applications, but my relationship with Java has not always been what one would call ideal. I much prefered programming languages which had a more natural flow to them, like a natural, spoken language. So I went out and looked for ways to code Android applications in a VB.Net-esque environment and I came across a few other IDE's like Delphi and Basic4Android but they were all expensive after their trial version and it was a period when money was hard to find for me. Long story short, I came across a certain line on a website, reading "Wanna be a developer? Any contributions can be made by any suggestions, codes related with java, c# and vb/vb.net on the core compiler or ide.". That is how I met Chengwei and how we became a team. I want to mention that no matter how young I was and how useless I thought I would be to the older, more experience coders, he has always been supportive towards me and always appreciates any developments made on this project. So that is how I became a part of his one-man team and how we started working on it together.After a long time Lu Told me that he didn't have that much time as long as he had to work for his job... as a result to give me the source code and as well the opportunity to work on the compiler by myself, as always with a confidence and trustfulness upon me, something i'll never forget about him."

data.name: RichTextBox2.Text
data.value:
"Me? I'm Chengwei from China, a 27 years old air quality modeler, and programming is my hobby..
I had my first Android phone after my moto ezx one in 2010. It was an HTC magic and it was the phone that made me beliveve that smart phones can make more than a phone with a good programming language. at that time google released the first version of "Simple" but with no IDE. While I had the ezx, I made a program named aslbas, an basic interpretor based on an unknown version of bas. Afterwards, I made up my mind to build an ide for Simple and name it "vb4android". I programmed the IDE myself and made extensions on the compiler. Sadly, I am not a good programmer, so even after 12 versions of vb4android I still had a buggy IDE. That was the time I finished my master degree candidate and started my job in CDAES as a member of the air quality research staff. That left me with little time to work on the development of vb4android v13 but, thanks to Giorgos, we now have a new, fully functional IDE"
